posts.cooked: Repositories.csv file is more than 25 Mb, its not allowing to upload , what to do

posts.name: Bahni Roy
posts.cooked:
That should not have been the case.
My repository file is ~2.5MB and contains close to 30k records.

Can you review the user details query and see if the applicable filters are present (as mentioned in the project description)? Review the count of the distinct loginids.

A 25MB repositories file indicate that way too many users have been fetched in the initial query (because the repositories result set is based off of that number).

@21f3000745

Q1, Q2, Q3, Q8 and Q14 you don’t need to put a space between them, just put a comma.

Q12 and Q15 might be wrong because you didn’t convert True to true and False to false.

There was one more mistake you made while extracting data, for repositories data you need to extract name from license but you extracted key, that will affect answer of Q3.

Q9, Q11 both are regarding correlation so that might be reason you are getting it wrong.

another reason for Q11 might be because you didn’t handle boolean’s correctly.
